        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">This will<lb/> be presented by <persName>Mr. I E. Bair</persName> of
                this<lb/> city, who also as kind enough to<lb/> take charge of a small package<lb/>
                for you from the <persName>Rev Dr Hirsch</persName><lb/>
                <persName>Mr B.</persName> is a respectable young man<lb/> our coreligionist and the
                son<lb/> of a <add>?</add> mother with seven<lb/> children besides himself, it is<lb/>
                <sic>unecessary</sic> to add that you<lb/> will do all you can to promote<lb/> his
                welfare in our happy<lb/> land whither he sends<add>?</add> himself<lb/> like
                thousands of his country=<lb/>man to seek the fortune of<lb/> himself and dependent
                family<lb/> any assistance in the way of<lb/> advice or otherwise you can<lb/>
                render him I will esteem as<lb/> a special favor and will consider</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the same as to self.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Have the<lb/> kindness to present your<lb/> Bill to my Banker
                    <persName>Messrs<lb/> David</persName> for payment. I have<lb/> received but two
                copies of<lb/> your weekly paper since its<lb/> commencement and only received<lb/>
                7 out of the 12 copies the preceding<lb/> time, have the kindness<lb/> and direct
                them to me in<lb/> person, the same as you do<lb/>
                <persName>Dr Hirsch</persName>' and they will come <lb/>safe to hand, say
                    <persName>Levi Dyer</persName><lb/>
                <placeName>No 27 Mainzer Chaupa<add>?</add><lb/> Frankfort</placeName></p>
            <p>How comes it you did not<lb/> republish the two letters of<lb/> mine in Hirsch'
                monthly. No 5—<lb/> and 7 appertaining to the welfare<lb/> and interests of some
                    <sic>Brethern</sic><lb/> in <placeName>Palestine</placeName><lb/>
                <persName>Ella E. Cozens</persName></p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Excuse haste &amp; believe me<lb/> to be yours at command</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">S<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Frankfort</placeName>
            </p>
            <p><date>Dec 21/59</date><lb/> Lucien</p>
        </body>
